  "text": "I'm ready to expand my HA system and seeking advice for HA controllable plug in outlets for the US market.\nEnergy monitoring would be nice to have, but last state recovery after a power outage is a must.  Either wifi or zigbee, although I don't yet have a zigbee connection to HA, so recommendations for a good zigbee interface.  Does the esp32-c6 qualify as good?  Don't want a USB one as my HA is virtualized on proxmox and the server is in the basement shop, so would prefer wifi or ethernet.  I checked the hadevices.com site but not enough info there, or is there a better site for HA compatible kit?",
